    "question_id" : 6950960,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Windows, open <code>cmd</code>.</p>\n<p>Go to the directory where your NetBeans file downloaded.</p>\n<p>Then run the below command. The JDK path may be different from the path I mentioned.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>netbeans-8.2-windows.exe --javahome &quot;C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk-9.0.1&quot;\n</code></pre>\n"
