    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user1328876"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1633346347,
    "last_edit_date" : 1633346347,
    "creation_date" : 1534603429,
    "answer_id" : 51909784,
    "question_id" : 6950960,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Where you already have a project in NetBeans and you wish to change the compiler (e.g. from  1.7 to 1.) then you would need to also change the Java source compiler for that project.</p>\n<p>Right-click on the project and choose <em>Properties</em> as outlined below:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/iFjDw.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/iFjDw.png\" alt=\"Java Project Properties\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then check that the project has the necessary source circled below:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jmR2o.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jmR2o.png\" alt=\"Project Source Compiler\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then check that the Java compiler is correct for the project:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/QQ5ov.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/QQ5ov.png\" alt=\"Enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5530214,
      "reputation" : 3302,
      "user_id" : 4722577,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52c9eff692173c0565797d23ee7e9794?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "CAMD_3441",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4722577/camd-3441"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1695921558,
    "creation_date" : 1695921558,
    "answer_id" : 77197056,
    "question_id" : 6950960,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For Apache Netbeans IDE 17 go to <code>Tools -&gt; Java Platforms</code>:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/J1WTb.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/J1WTb.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then in the <code>Java Platform Manager</code> click on <code>Add Platform...</code>:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/fr7M6.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/fr7M6.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>Then go through the next menu options and select the jdk version you downloaded that you want to add to netbeans, then click on <code>Finish</code>, now you'll see a new platform listed with the jdk you just added:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/RNehb.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/RNehb.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>Now go to <code>Tools -&gt; Options</code> then go to the <code>Java -&gt; Maven</code> tab and for the <code>Default JDK</code> option you can now select the new jdk you added above:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TPJOP.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TPJOP.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p>Now when you compile your application on Netbeans you can see the Java version it is using:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/bNSuR.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/bNSuR.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  } ],
